'So bottom line is: outstanding athletes, outstanding organization, outstanding team but also outstanding members of their community,' Obama said.

He wished them 'great luck' for the rest of the current season, 'unless they're playing the (Chicago) Bulls,' Obama's hometown and favorite NBA team.

Coach Erik Spoelstra presented Obama with a commemorative championship trophy that lists the players' names as well as Obama's.

The president also received an autographed basketball and team jersey with the number '44' and 'POTUS' on the back.

